<b><font color="#800080"> 18th March: </font></b>
<b> Assorted</b> (Southampton - GR)
<p>
<b> Bring a fun paper</b>
<p>

This week we will have an informal "show and tell". The idea is to choose a paper/article that you find interesting and tell the rest of the group about it, it can be either crank theory or of genuine scientific interest.<p>

Here are links to the papers
Lucy Keer
<i>Cooke and Rand - A mathematical study of resonance in intact fruits and 
vegetables using a 3-media elastic sphere model </i>
<p>
Vanessa Graber
<a href=http://arxiv.org/abs/0809.0339> John G. Learned, R-P. Kudritzki, Sandip Pakvasa, A. Zee - <i>  The Cepheid Galactic Internet</i> </a>
<p>
Stephanie Erickson
<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1205.5233"> E. S. Benilov, C. P. Cummins, W. T. Lee - <i>  Why do bubbles in Guinness sink?</i> </a>
