<!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<hr>
<b><font color="#800080"> 11th March: </font></b>
<b>Marta Colleoni</b> (Southampton - GR)
<p>
<b> Symmetries and symmetry breaking in QFT </b>
<p>

I will talk about the role that symmetries play in QFT and go through some relevant examples. I will then explain the concept of symmetry breaking and show how it led to predict the existence of the Higgs boson.
&nbsp;

<p>
<A HREF="QFT2.pdf">
[download talk]
</A>



<A HREF="http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=xUHQ2ybTejU">
[Crab Canon]
</A>


<!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<hr>
<b><font color="#800080"> 4th March: </font></b>
<b> Matthew Spraggs </b> (Southampton - CMG)
<p>
<b> Complexity and the Edge of Chaos </b>
<p>
We give an overview of complexity science and why it is necessary to revise our approach to the study of certain systems. We follow this with several examples of complex systems, and finish by looking at what the future holds for the study of complexity.
&nbsp;

<p>
<A HREF="Mathew_Spraggs_apgr_03_2013.pdf">
[download talk]
</A>



<A HREF="riddle2.pdf">
[Riddle]
</A>




<!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<hr>
<b><font color="#800080"> 25th Febuary: </font></b>
<b>Marc Scott</b> (Southampton - SHEP)
<p>
<b> An introduction to the ideas of String Theory </b>
<p>
We begin with an overview of the basic ideas behind String Theory and why it is necessary to consider them. We then turn to look at a classical bosonic string theory scenario for a more in depth look at the mathematics required for such a theory.
&nbsp;
<p>
<A HREF="Marc_Scott_apgr_02_2013.pdf">
[download talk]
</A>

<A HREF="riddle1.pdf">
[Riddle]
